      <h1 class="section-heading centered white">Usage and endpoints:</h1>
      <p class="paragraph-2">A request made to LYD Stats API starts with the following:</p>
      <p class="paragraph-3">www.lydstats.com/LYD/</p>
      <p class="paragraph-4">The user must then add two parameters separated by a &quot;/&quot;. The first  is the base currency of the price required, and the second  is the date of the price.<br><br><strong>Base</strong> <strong>Currency</strong>: the user can choose one of 6 base currencies available. The ISO4217 code of these currencies should be entered. These currencies, in their ISO codes are: USD, GBP, EUR, TND, TRY, CNY.<br>‍<br>e.g. if the user wants to obtain a price for GBP, they must add the currency as follows:<br></p>
      <p class="paragraph-3">www.lydstats.com/LYD/GBP</p>
      <p class="paragraph-4"><strong>Price Date:</strong> after the currency, the user must add a date to the URL, they may enter an actual date in the format: YYYY-MM-DD if a specific date is required, or enter the word &quot;Today&quot; if the user wants to get the price of the request date. for example:<br></p>
      <p class="paragraph-3">www.lydstats.com/LYD/GBP/2020-11-18</p>
      <p class="paragraph-4 space"><strong>or:</strong><br></p>
      <p class="paragraph-3">www.lydstats.com/LYD/GBP/Today</p>
      <p class="paragraph-4">The API will return a standard JSON response including the price information. <br></p>
      <p class="paragraph-4">It is also possible to insert &quot;listquotes&quot; as a parameter in order to get a list of the currencies covered by the API.<br></p>
      <p class="paragraph-3">www.lydstats.com/LYD/listquotes</p>
    </div>
